				<strong><font color="4a0000">The Official "So-Called" Strategy Guide</strong></font><br>
				</center>
              </td>
            </tr>
			<tr>
              <td width="100%" bgcolor="CDCD9C" background="">
              <p align="center"><font face="arial" size="2">News Contributed By:
              <a href="mailto:dantes@eqrealms.com"><font color="ca0000"><b>Dantes</a></b></font><br>
              </font><font face="arial" size="1">Thursday, May 4, 2000</font></td>
            </tr>
			<tr>
              <td width="100%" bgcolor="CDCD9C">
                &nbsp;
                <div align="center">
                  <center>
                  <table border="0" width="98%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%"><font face="arial" size="2">So how many of you folks picked up the official Everquest Ruins of Kunark Strategy Guide from Prima?  I'll admit, I don't have a copy but I am still busting a gut laughing at some of the quotes from it that people have quoted on the gameplay boards.  Most of the players have said they can't imagine why anyone would want to actually spend money on it, rather than to have a good laugh.  I remember Verant was even mentioning that they had more of a hand in this guide, from the looks of it the writer has never even played EverQuest.  I'm just curious on who has it, what blunders have you found inside, and how do you think this makes Verant look?</font>
                        <p>&nbsp;
					  </td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  </center>
                </div>
              </td>
            </tr>
			<tr>
              <td width="100%" bgcolor="CDCD9C" background="">
                <p align="center"><font face="arial" size="2"><b>Responses to This
                Post:</b></font></td>
            </tr>
	
	        
	 
	        <tr>
              <td width="100%" bgcolor="CDCD9C">
                &nbsp;
                <div align="center">
                  <center>
                  <table border="0" width="98%" cellspacing="1" bgcolor="000000" cellpadding="2">
				  
				    <tr>
                      <td width="6%" valign="top" align="center" bgcolor="bfbf80" background=""><font face="arial" color="4a0000" size="3"><b>1.</b></font></td>
                      <td width="94%" valign="top" bgcolor="CDCD9C"><font face="arial" size="2"><b>Response from:
                        <a href="mailto:dantes@eqrealms.com"><font color="ca0000">Dantes</font></a></b>
                        </font><font face="arial" size="1"> - Thursday, May 4, 2000 at 5:34 PM</font><font face="arial" size="2"><br>
						
						
						Ok here are some of my favorites I've found so far, this is hilarious.  This is an official strategy guide folks, people may money for this:<p>"As a Dwarven Warrior, you can wear a full suit of bronze armor - no other race can do so."  Really? Hmm I guess I've seen a lot of tall dwarves wearing bronze then.<p>"Warrior. Because of their size, Dwarves are harder to hit in combat."  Yeah whatever.<p>(Dwarves) "Short legs. For obvious reasons, Dwarves have a hard time running away from their opponents."  Oh, yeah, is that the same reason why humans find it hard to run away from opponents as well?<p>"Like a viper. Gnomes can strike fast in combat and move out of the way even faster." Someone needs to ask Abashi if Gnomes have built in haste, last time I checked THEY DON'T. LOL<p>"Only the Wizard can take people to the Planes of Sky and Hate, but she shouldn't."<p>Shadowknight - "Vs. red NPCs. Best to party with strong characters and Clerics." Um, isn't that the way it is with any class?  You mean if I don't choose Shadow Knight I can solo reds?<p>Rangers - "Go for max damage. Given the choice between 2-Handed Slash and 1-Handed Slash, remember that 2-Handed does more damage. 1-Handed is great with a shield, but then, shields are heavy, and there's the encumbrance issue ... and Rangers don't get Bash, anyway. So, unless, there's a good reason not to, go for the 1-Handed Slash." The 1H or the 2H?  Do you know what dual wield is?  <p>Monks - "Don't even try to learn a weapon." Ok, I guess all those Monk only weapons Verant put into the game are useless anyways.<p>
						
						</font>
					  </td>
                    </tr>
					 
					
				    <tr>
